The item was designed for when you need a ListItem control but your list is generated at runtime, for example a position control on an axis, where the player can increase or decrease a position by e.g. 0.01. Before this control you'd need to generate a list of all numbers in a range (or better, generate three, prev, current and next).  Now you can use this item and respond dynamically to list changes.

Example:
````C#
var car = ...

var menu = new UIMenu("example", "example");
var list = new UIMenuDynamicListItem("Heading", car.Heading.ToString("F2"), (sender, direction) =>
{
    if (direction == ChangeDirection.Left) car.Heading += 0.01f;
    else car.Heading -= 0.01f;
    return car.Heading.ToString("F2"); // New label
});

menu.AddItem(list);
...
````

